KEY FEATURES:

Web Scraping

Text Embedding Generation

Database Storage

Semantic Search

LLM-powered Question Answering

PREREQUESITES:

R and the following packages
rvest
RSQLite
httr
openai (if using the OpenAI API)
Hugging Face API key
OpenAI API key
Usage:

INSTALL NECESSARY PACKAGES:
Code snippet
install.packages(c("rvest", "RSQLite", "httr", "openai")) 

REPLACE PLACEHOLDERS:
Hugging Face API Key: Replace "your_huggingface_api_key" with your actual Hugging Face API key in the convert_to_embeddings function.
OpenAI API Key: Replace "your_api_key" with your actual OpenAI API key in the generate_response function.
Run the script:
Execute the code.
The script will scrape the specified website, generate embeddings, store them in the database, and demonstrate the question-answering process with a sample query.

This Readme provides a basic overview of the code. For detailed explanations of each function and its purpose, refer to the comments within the code itself.

Disclaimer: This code is provided for educational and illustrative purposes only. The use of external APIs may have associated costs. Please refer to the respective API providers' terms of service for details.
  
